# Next.js frontend rules

Read `.ai/stack-frontend-nextjs.md` for full detail.

- Server Components by default; add "use client" only when interactivity is required.
- Fetch on the server where possible; React Query for client data/mutations.
- Keep business logic out of components — extract to hooks/lib.
- TypeScript strict; no `any` without a justifying comment; validate external data with zod.
- Handle all async states: loading, empty, error, success.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, keyboard nav, visible focus, AA contrast.
- No secrets client-side (only NEXT_PUBLIC_*); auth tokens in HttpOnly cookies.
- Tests: vitest + Testing Library for units, Playwright for E2E. Lint + typecheck must pass.

